cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new solution for learning recommender systems from user multi-behavior data using a neural network model. It also involves joint optimization based on the multi-task learning framework. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with the problem of recommending items to users based on their behavior data. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of recommender systems. 

It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with user behavior data and the interactions between users and items. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing techniques to analyze user behavior data such as views, clicks, and adding products to shop carts.
